name: Lindsey Taylor
text: Quiet but not too bad. Staff were slow to clear tables but the lunch buffet never ran out of food.

name: Bkiss SextonWildcats
text: Perfect if you have small kids, it's not busy, but the food is great!

name: KSStorm Info
text: Ordered BBQ beef pizza. Got ground beef on BBQ sauce. Totally not what I was looking for. One of the few Pizza Huts still in the original mansard roof buildings... I was hoping for a bit of nostalgia, but this one looks like it's last interior remodel was in the early 90s. Don't think I'll be going back to this location.

name: Micheal Johnson
text: service wasn't very good. had the buffet and the salad was old and turning brown.

name: smell my turtle
text: Awful. Only one person working during lunch. Cold pizza on buffet. Bad service. Dirty. Close it already.

name: Glen Williams sr.
text:
Good food, good service, but filthy rest rooms!
Any place that serves food should have clean rest rooms! No excuses whatsoever. Hire a cleaning crew if you're that busy. The health department' would have a field day,  hint hint!

name: Cody Gaul
text: Ordered a double order of breadsticks and Chiken Alfredo and they gave me rotten, fermented Marinara with it. Literal mold floating in it and smelled like straight beer. Took a bite of it not noticing and threw up. WILL NEVER EAT HERE AGAIN. I do not reccomend eating here whatsoever.

name: Dan Wiegand
text: This is a old school Pizza Hut     sandwiches are wonderful

name: Kristopher Martin
text: Great and friendly staff. Very nice to my daughter and wife.

name: sarah akred
text: Fast service & friendly staff. Pizza was good

name: Dan Madrigal
text: The pizza was good and friendly service

name: Michael St Claire Jr
text: Bring back the fresh dough.

name: Hawns Osborne
text:
Great customer service evertime we go in.
Maybe they should train the employees at the
newer pizza hut on maize road.  Worth the
Little drive into maize.

name: Dale Browers
text: Always  clean  friendly staff  and good  food

name: ami jewell
text: Been the same for years ..Bob Dole dined here...the land before time commercial was filmed here too....

name: Derek Purcell
text: The staff that my family dealt with was awesome! Very helpful and accommodating. I love this Pizza Hut because it is the only one I know that has not been remodeled. It's like a trip down memory lane. I love it!

name: Wes Trivitt
text: Last remaining classic Pizza Hut in the area. Best food and service out of this side of town.

name: Peter Spexarth
text: Best pizza for the affordable prices! Staff is very friendly and accommodating. Dine-in has a great, chill atmosphere.

name: Bob Parsons
text: Good service at lunch. Staff offered and made Pizza for the buffet when the things they had out were not to our liking. Made a pizza just for us to put on buffet! Wonderful service!!

name: Susan Pitzer
text: This Pizza Hut was the best. Now they almost gave me the wrong pizzas. I caught the mistake. My food was on sale but I paid the wrong pizzas price. Not a good experience this visit, JAKE. Try better next time, JAKE.

name: Zachary Zugelder
text: Went in for lunch. Having been eatting there for years. I had the buffet the salad bar was just a mess no salad just dirty as can be. The pizza was just awful hard as a brick. The kid waiting on my table never offered to fill a tea glass. Horrible service I didn't leave a tip won't be back!!!!

name: Craig Siebert
text: Very friendly helpful employees

name: Lyle Rease Cason Jr
text:
Bathrooms were sub par, dilapidated and run down.
While we waited for our order, they were having some sort of staff meeting virtually right behind us. â€¦More

name: Aaron
text: Good food, one of the last locations that is set up primarily for dine-in. I believe this is the last Pizza Hut in town that still has anchovies available as an option on their pizzas as well...just a fun fact.

name: K Google
text: Awesome nostalgic

name: Bryan Horsewood Sr.
text: Got the p'zone. Not very good. Not enough pepperoni or cheese, too doughy and dipping sauce is bland.

name: Julie Brawner
text: Very disappointed.  Pizza was over cooked and the restaurant wasn't very clean. Took over 30 minutes to get our order. Used to enjoy coming here, hadn't been here in several months,  won't be coming back

name: Stephanie Stewart
text: Love the knots
